    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Poles, rods, sticks, or stakes placed in a horizontal position and used for any of various purposes, typically as a prop or support. Examples include bars provided as resting places for birds, rods supporting the body of a cart, bars on which to hang clothes or other things, and bars over which pieces of cloth or leather are secured for working.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000114707/Oxford English Dictionary Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000093853/Webster's Third New International Dictionary (2002)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Palen, roedes, stokken of staven die in een horizontale positie worden gebruikt voor diverse doeleinden, vooral als stut of steun. Bijvoorbeeld stokjes waar vogels op zitten, staven die de carrosserie van een wagen ondersteunen, staven om kleren of andere dingen overheen te hangen en staven waaroverheen stukken doek of leer worden bevestigd om te worden bewerkt.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099090/Van Dale Online Woordenboek (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000109894/UvA Talen</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Pali, aste, o bastoncini posizionati in posizione orizzontale e utilizzati per vari scopi, in genere come supporto. Esempi includono sprange che forniscono luoghi di riposo per uccelli, aste che sostengono il corpo di un carrello, barre su cui appendere vestiti o altre cose, e barre su cui sono fissati pezzi di stoffa o pelle per il lavoro.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Italian</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
